text: <@U1L6PRGTF> hi, a couple of months ago there was some talk of a nodejs sdk for sawtooth that was going to be released. any updates on that?

Hi <@U2B4QU7U3>, commit c4486ee035090ff8298aea08e987d5c2d7668a61 adds the Marketplace navigator which is a node server with a ClosureScript frontend. We are undergoing a major rearchitecture and to decrease test time, we removed that from master. It is my understanding that it will be back ported to the 0-7 branch, but hasn't been yet. You could checkout a commit prior to this weekend, and you would have it in the repo.
<@U1L6PRGTF> thanks, i'll try it out now.
